        "message": "I\u2019m not able to modify the file from here because the remote host isn\u2019t reachable via SSH.  \nTo finish the remediation on your Rocky\u202fLinux machine, just run the following commands:\n\n```bash\n# 1. Create (or overwrite) the sudoers include file\ncat <<'EOF' > /etc/sudoers.d/selinux_sudo\n%wheel ALL=(ALL) TYPE=sysadm_t ROLE=sysadm_r ALL\nEOF\n\n# 2. Set the correct permissions and ownership\nchmod 0440 /etc/sudoers.d/selinux_sudo\nchown root:root /etc/sudoers.d/selinux_sudo\n\n# 3. Verify the syntax so you don\u2019t lock out sudo\nvisudo -cf /etc/sudoers.d/selinux_sudo\n```\n\nAfter the `visudo` check reports *Syntax OK*, the rule is applied and the finding is remediated.  \nIf you need any further help or a different file\u2011level change, let me know!",
